718080f-a.title: Manhattan: Cannon Street - Broome Street
718080f-a.text:
Cannon Street, north from and including Broome Street. Also shon
aoross the vacant lot at the S.W. corner, is Nos. 68-70 and a portion of
No. 72 Broome Street, at adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Cannon
Street.
February 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
718080f-a.folder: Cannon Street & Broome Street, Manhattan, NY

717850f-a.title: Manhattan: Broome Street - Cannon Street
717850f-a.text:
Broome Street. west from Cannon Street. Note the park in
the right center (just beyond the soiitary No. 82 Broome) where
the north R. Hoe and Co. plant formerly stood. Barely discernible
on the left is the modern apartment house facing on same.
NEG~ 3E57  May 7, 1939
P. L. Sperr
717850f-a.folder: Broome Street & Cannon Street, Manhattan, NY

718079f-b.title: Manhattan: Cannon Street - Broome Street
718079f-b.text:
Cannon Street, north from a podnt between Broome and
Delancey Streets and across the latter.
The Williamsburg Bridge is overhead and View No. 2 is from
its base. Wote the vacant lots at the N.E. and N. W. corners.
May 7, 1939
Views: 1 and 2
P. L. Sperr
